# 📧 Phishing Detection System — Complete Instructions

## 📋 Prerequisites

- **Python 3.10+** installed on your system
- **Internet connection** (required for DNS lookups, WHOIS queries, and website analysis)

---

## 🔧 Step 1: Setup (One-Time)

Open a terminal (Command Prompt or PowerShell) and navigate to the project folder:

```powershell
cd C:\Users\rajvi\Downloads\phishing_detection_system
```

### Create a Virtual Environment (if not already created)

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
```

### Activate the Virtual Environment

```powershell
.venv\Scripts\activate
```

> [!TIP]
> After activation, you should see `(.venv)` at the start of your terminal prompt.

### Install Dependencies

```powershell
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

This installs: `beautifulsoup4`, `requests`, `tldextract`, `dnspython`, `python-whois`, `cryptography`, `lxml`

